The paper discusses decision-making and classification, which are core topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). It also addresses the issue of strategic behavior and its impact on classification, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The concept of social burden and its disproportionate impact on disadvantaged groups relates to fairness and social implications of machine learning (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's focus on decision boundaries and robustness suggests a connection to statistical learning theory and data structures (cs.DS).
